Type: Indica/Sativa Hybrid
Cross: Grapefruit X Herojuana

The Dirty Harry marijuana strain is not named after Clint Eastwood. She's named because the female grapefruit bx1 smells and tastes very earthy, like dirt. Her Grapefruit mother was crossed with a male Blueberry and then crossed back again with another Grapefruit clone. The result is sweet, citrusy, earthy, berry goodness that will spin your head around and around! When the Herojuana was crossed in, bud density and stoneage strength was increased. The final result is a plant that grows easily, even for beginning home marijuana cultivators. This strain has truly strong genetics and needs only the basics to do her thing: intense lights, pure water, quality nutrients and carbon dioxide.

Picked up from Farmer's Market. This particular one was not all that impressive. Will try from dispensary next time.

Quite a pleasant feeling so far. Pungent odor, but in a good way. Sweet, berry, a little bit spicy, kinda earthy on the exhale.

Time has slowwwwwed down. Feels really nice though. I feel like I lost a chunk of time and saw that only 40 minutes have passed. Whoa!

Still have back pain, though. What if it's not muscular? Maybe it's skeletal? Can you fracture a rib on your back?

This particular batch of medication I picked up from Green Anne was among the best I've smoked in Seattle. Visually speaking, the bud was absolutely glazed. The scent was difficult to place, a thick herbal perfume overtone that ranged down to a sort of unusual mothball undertone - and I mean that in the best way possible. The taste upon vaping tended toward the herbal side, spicy, with maybe a touch of cinnamon. The high was wonderful. The world became brighter, more colorful, more alive. I felt zoned-in, hyper-aware, yet heavily stoned, and it lasted a full two hours. Highly recommended.

The smell is a strong apricot aroma, and the buds are dense with olive-green bud and red hairs. The smoke is sweet and nutty on the inhale, and spicy (think black pepper) on the exhale. It gets kind of harsh toward the end of the bowl so keep a drink handy. Uplifting, energizing, and empowering describe this strain's effects, and the experience is pleasant as a whole, though I would not recommend to those who are sensitive to strong sativas.

Blue OG is a pretty nice strain for afternoon and evening use
Very Smooth when you smoke it ! Make me laugh with my friends. Sticky weed. I like it !

This strain made its way down south from the great forward thinking state of michigan.. 

Appearance: Nice earth tones. Camo  greens and yellows with classic sienna pistils["hairs ;) ].. In bright daylight, the trichromes shine, giving it a glittery effect. 4/5

Texture: Buds are solid and stiff..A good halfway point between uberfluffy sativas and rock hard indica buds. Resinous and sticks to the fingers somewhat, but nothing overdramatic. 3/5

Smell: There is a mild fruit/blueberry smell present for which the strain is named.. However, the predominant aromas are that of pine and earth. Perhaps, this particular crop was grown outdoors? Upon a second trial, the blueberry smell is definitely there.. Overall, the weed has presence thru a ziplock bag, but definitely milder than some of the heavy indicas out there. 3/5

Taste: No fruitiness here..This pot is very earthy tasting with more of the pine overtones. It was definitely grown in a rich soil medium, whether indoors or out, as the taste is very evident on a fresh green hit. While evidence of soil growing is pleasant in its own right, the flavor was nothing particularly spectacular. The smoke is kind of harsh on the throat, perhaps do to it being a bit dry and a bit resinous. 3/5

Potency: This marijuana is a THC bomb! Surprisingly intoxicated off of one solid pipe hit..A couple of decent rips would put down a novice smoker. Not the strongest I've smoked in my life, but definitely more potent then the average grade A stuff. I can pack a single bowl and take single hits off this, and be as high as I comfortably want to get for an entire evening.. The high tends to be a creeper, the full effects setting in 20 minutes later, lending to a "holy shit!" sort of feeling :) Very impressed in this aspect. 5/5

Effects: Apparently this strain is a 60/40 Indica/Sativa hybrid. It may be that my last stash was 100% indica, but the sativa really shines thru on this strain, more so than the indica. Provided you havent retarded yourself by disrespecting the potency, the overall buzz of this pot is very social and chatty..extrospective..Movies and music are a blast as the herb helps pull all the richness and perhaps overlooked details of whatever entertainment you choose..This weed is light-hearted and fun(again, if you didnt subject yourself to multiple bong rips)..

The body high is pleasant and tingly..Some nice feelings of "stretchiness, melting, and energy waves" as the evening progresses. However, the euphoric analgesia and muscle relaxation isnt as profound as my former stash of indica. Maybe not the best weed for treatment of pain, this marijuana seems to be better suited for socializing.. While this bud provides a mental and social stimulation, it still leaves the body relaxed and lazy, unlike pure sativas that have me doing chores and hiking in the woods.. A nice well rounded high that is great for chilling around the house with friends or alone. Would work well at concerts, museums etc. also.

This pot didnt really give me the crucial munchies like some other weed..however sweet things and wine had exceptional flavors. I also slept perfectly fine[sometimes sativa dominant highs stimulate the mind enough to disrupt sleep for me]

Power-houring this weed however, will probably leave you pretty couch locked and spaced out, because you'll be too fucked up to do much else ;) Oh and a word of caution, this pot seems to mix well with beer and wine, but definitely will contribute to a feeling of drunkeness, if you are stupid enough to drive.  4/5

Ever wonder if some strains of pot could potentially fire your neurons in a somewhat random runaway kind of way? As in, your train of thought continues with your observation/perception of your experience, but your thoughts spark an idea, and suddenly a whole chain of neurons of related ideas is set afire. It takes off like a lit fuse to an explosion, and runs away from your control of your immediate attention span (for 10-40 seconds in my experience). "And then before you know it" happens still later! I'd had myself a small world of a daydream in itself. It reached a quick crescendo-- it felt like my adrenaline/endorphins/happychems topped off-- and then reached a sudden, if pleasingly satisfactory, stop. The train of thought had completed itself. At that moment existence was a mini pause and I remembered where I was now, and before, and was able to refocus my perception to zoom out and see the entire journey I'd taken in its small entirety of ~15 seconds (for me. also depends on the thought). The train of thought because an independent thought with a life of its own. A new tree in my neural network kingdom. I will wander back to it and climb it again some day soon.

I described all this to my SO, asking if the whole neuron firing thing was possible on certain kinds of pot/brainchemcombo. He agreed it was a plausible description. Therefore it may be in agreement to other peoples' experiences as well. So I figured I'd share.

Other details:
My attention span itself is shook up in a sprinkled scattered kind of way. Everything in my senses lends itself to the experience of thought development, so whatever you think of is somehow made of everything present, in a perfect way. Music is the soundtrack to your thoughts in a much deeper way than before, somewhat overtaking your attention span.

The runaway firing is fun-- to see where it takes you, and what fun, awesome ideas you find there-- but I also sense the loss of control in a somewhat bad way. In general, I say that pot "gives me ADHD" (I am not diagnosed as such), because my attention span singularizes, and thus I lose decent multitasking function. It's pretty silly sometimes. Like, I'll be doing something while lucid that keeps my concentration focused on it quite precisely yet without much effort. Then I have a few puffs off the vape, and suddenly the task I was doing before becomes much harder to think about and remember what I'm supposed to do with it next.

There's also a rather significant split in myself, it almost seems... Part of me ends up in a continuous loop of realizing/remembering what's going on, and then diving into it trying to get back into the feel and journey of the thought, only to lose myself again-- as it tumbled away in rapids and currents. Only to end up back at the realization moment again.

The rest of me has bought the ticket and taken the ride-- another seed of my attention/consciousness follows the fuse light along its path. It has a full, rewarding life before sputtering out like the neuron chain. It even contributes to the free association and thus development of the chain, if that makes any sense. And it's also what comes back to my other brain to tell the tale. :)

In the end, this review is a tale of two (primary, anyway) thought trains, always meeting in the middle and then circling away again.

PS: I don't mean looping in the repetitive way. (Ask me about what time looks like animated sometime.)

  I'm a light smoker, so I usually smoke about a 1/4 of my blunt and then put it out. I do this to enjoy my high and to also build my tolerance back up to what it used to be. If I take a larger hit, my nose and soft palate feel tingly afterwards. I am a moderate smoker, and find that I am still able to do things during the day, yet unwind at the end of the day with this strain. It's almost like this strain allows you to pick if you want to be up and around, or slow down and chill. If I smoke too much of this though, I do get a heavier indica effect; lose focus and couch lock. So just be conservative with the day-usage your first time, maybe. I suffer from severe menstrual cramps, and moderate back pain, and this took my pain away within the first 10 minutes. Overall, it's not my favorite hybrid, but it's definitely a good one.

After much research, I was happy to find out that this would have no ill effect.  The buds were really thick and dense.  I was under the impression that this was more of an indica dominant hybrid.  If it is a total indica then you might be happy to know that it isn't a super heavyweight hitter or a 'de-motivator', but it has a killer buzz none the less. One of my all-time favorites from a local collective storefront here in town (CC) who prefers to stay on the dl as this socially conservative California city mainly sees storefronts of the type as persona non-Grata, though the climate is changing palpably. 

This strain is directly grown by them and seems to be superior in appearance, smell, taste and effect than other NC Fire OG labels in the same geographic area.  You will experience a nice smoke, not harsh but still with some punch to live up to the Fire name.  The immediate effect that I felt after smoking (glass pipe) was a relief of joint pain, anxiety and a noticeable shift of focus and awareness towards present.  I think this train deserves to be smoked in a high-tech glass water-rig to get the full flavor.

To my nose, it has a moderate earthy smell, with a steady sweet after-tone and a very minimal if not a complete lack there of chemical smell.  I would be happy to hear but not surprised if this strain was grown using organic nutrients in a high quality soil/hydro and environment.

No lab tests to be found however I am curious to find out.  Also, to see if this strain would be effective in other forms in addition to the beautiful flower could be something worth exploring if that has not been done already.  The greens are pleasant and the contrast to the orange hairs is compelling.  Trichomes are rich and coat the overall slightly leafy appearance consistently. So if you're after overly-dense nugs, this strain might not satisfy but don't let that cloud the true quality of this superb medicine.

Excellent aroma smells super skunky, but then turns minty in the flavor. Hits hard and lasts for awhile. Really lets you focus and get into whatever you're doing, and keeps a smile on your face while you do it.

Look: Mid green color with tons of red hairs. It looked like herb. :) which is always good.

Touch: Mid size buds, solid but not dense and fluffy but not too airy.

Smell: Sweet and Fruity. Very pleasant. Smells like herb, which is good.

Taste: Not the best tasting cannabis. First drag tasted good, the rest were a bit harsh. Decent taste off and on throughout the smoke.

The Smoke: Grinder/Joint - semi- harsh smoke. The effects came on about 10-15 minutes after first drag. An hour later, I forget the semi-harsh smoke because the CBD kicked in.

Effect: Happy, Euphoric, Laughing at the Bing Bang Theory and the Pete Holmes Show. I feel a bit more of the THC than I expected. Definitely felt the CBD. Started feeling relaxed and mentally stimulated at the same time.

Before smoke: Tight neck and shoulders. Inflammation from Arthritis. Specifically back, ankles, hips, hands and fingers. Sore muscles from heavy walking. General surge of anxiety throughout my body.

After smoke: I still felt tight in neck and shoulders. After 20 minutes the effects started to sink in. After an hour, my body felt very relaxed in an uncomfortable sitting position. Good sign. I would have been constantly adjusting my body to find comfort, if not for this flower. My pain is there but it's not there. I can be aware of it, but it doesn't bother me. When I laid down, I felt very relaxed.

Conclusion: This strain was advertised as 8.12% CBD & 4.19% THC, I would say that is about right. I would prefer a 10% or more CBD and less that 4% THC. If I vaporized or smoked out of a bubbler or smoked more, I may of had more of a relief.

Bio Jesus is one of the frostiest and most potent strains of cannabis I have ever encountered. I purchased this indica-dominant hybrid sample from Denver Relief, being very impressed with the bag/jar appeal. The bud would simply appear light green with light orange hairs if it weren't completely covered in trichomes, giving it an almost white appearance. Despite some mild fox-tailing, the buds are pretty dense. Bio Jesus has a light and crisp aroma that smells of a vague floral scent with hints of tropical fruits. When the buds are broken into a sharp pine flavor emerges. The flavor is reminiscent of the smell, except for the overwhelming chest-expansion and nose-biting. The herbal and spicy smoke is not unpleasant, but certainly harsh even through a water filtered device. Vaporizing is the best way to experience the complex bouquet of Bio Jesus. The buzz is perhaps the best thing about this stain, however. After one good hit, even a seasoned smoker with a high tolerance will begin to feel  the effects of this strong indica. Bio Jesus may cause happiness, sleepiness, increased appetite, relaxation, and dry mouth. A fantastic medicine for night-time or when being productive is not important.

This is my first review so bare with me. Fruity Pebbles is an interesting strain. It is a nice balanced cross between an indica and sativa, but from my experience with it I'd say it's a little bit more indica dominant due to the  nice body high it provides! 

Appearance: A nice bright green with bright orange hairs. The main thing I noticed was that there was very little trichomes covering the buds which made me a little skeptical at first.

Smoke & Aroma: 
Staying true to it's name this strain really does smell like a form Fruity Pebbles although to me it smelt more like Fruit Loops. The smoke is very smooth on the lungs, it's not harsh at all leaving you with a nice mildly fruity and creamy aroma on the exhale! "Just like smoking a cereal..."

Effects & Experience:
After smoking one joint (sprinkled with kief) the high started to take effect in about 5 minutes. It started off with a mellow head high then dawned down straight into a body high. Walking became a little difficult and my legs became heavy, but I felt very euphoric / positive. It isn't the most potent strain but it still provides a very relaxing fun high; not so overbearing.  I'm still relatively a new smoker so I don't have a very high tolerance.

Duration:
The high last for about 2 - 2 1/2 hours. Tolerance differences may vary.
 
Overall:
I would Fruity Pebbles is just right for hanging out with your friends, playing video games, going to a sports game, going to the beach, going to the movies, and ect...  I'd definitely recommend this strain anybody that just wants a comfortable relaxing high.

Out of all the strains I've tried, this one definitely leads the pack as far as treating insomnia go. Also, as opposed to other strains that induce couch lock, sleepiness, relaxation, or any other form of lethargy, this strain doesn't cause that much trouble maintaining focused thoughts; the main noticeable effect is the overall relaxation and desire to rest.

The aroma is earthy, flowery, sweet - maybe a bit fruity, maybe a bit like moist earth. The color is deep green, with little specks of orange in it. A little hairy, but not that much. It tastes earthy and sweet, and leaves a unique aftertaste.

Since I live in the Los Angeles area, this strain is actually quite common, but that doesn't make it any less amazing. Stress, depression, anxiety, and insomnia sufferers take note: Try this strain out if you have access to it.

Overall, the potency is somewhat high. It's very easy to stretch this one a bit, as the couch lock and overwhelming need to close your eyes will come very easily, so you won't want to overuse it. If that's something you're looking for, this is definitely one strain you don't want to leave your dispensary without trying.

Picked up a quarter of this strain at my local dispensary as flowers, went home and upon smelling it I immediately decided to try it. I ended up smoking all of it in one session between my two friends and I; I rolled a blunt and smoked it myself while we all passed around my friend's bong. The first thing about this weed I noticed was the exceptionally strong odor. The second thing I noticed was the harshness of smoke. If you want a strain you enjoy by tasting, this is definitely not that strain (I'd try either fruity pebbles or strawberry crunch for that). However, the effects of Platinum OG are strong and fast, and the buzz refused to back down for quite a few hours. Great for medical use with very spacey/stoney effects. I did noticed I was a bit more focused than when I usually smoke that much with other pure indica strains. I almost confused it as a sativa dominant hybrid when I tried it at first. Either way, this is a top grade strain with top grade medical value. I'd highly recommend it to anyone.

This is a great strain for beginner medical users or for people who want to savor the taste of their weed. The smoke is scary smooth; I easily filled my whole chamber in my bong with dense, milky smoke and held each hit for 15-20 seconds, which is not how I usually do it, but I was able to with this strain. The nugs are extremely unique looking, with curly leaves and bubbly, light creamy green edges that made it look good enough to eat. I noticed that everything about this strain is light; the color, the smoke, and unfortunately the effects. The buzz barely lasted for an hour and a half, and I probably smoked 2 g's by myself in the session preceding. I could get the same buzz from barely .25 g of Northern lights or Bubba kush. However, to end on a good note, this cannabis proves useful in that it doesn't give you a headache, it makes you laugh, talk and be more social in general and it tastes delicious.

Purple OG tastes like a Christmas tree that has been rolled in grape fun-dip. A creeper indica that settles into the body and head causing relaxation, mood lift, and the munchies. Bio Jesus is one of the frostiest and most potent strains of cannabis I have ever encountered. I purchased this indica-dominant hybrid sample from Denver Relief, being very impressed with the bag/jar appeal. The bud would simply appear light green with light orange hairs if it weren't completely covered in trichomes, giving it an almost white appearance. Despite some mild fox-tailing, the buds are pretty dense. Bio Jesus has a light and crisp aroma that smells of a vague floral scent with hints of tropical fruits. When the buds are broken into a sharp pine flavor emerges. The flavor is reminiscent of the smell, except for the overwhelming chest-expansion and nose-biting. The herbal and spicy smoke is not unpleasant, but certainly harsh even through a water filtered device. Vaporizing is the best way to experience the complex bouquet of Bio Jesus. The buzz is perhaps the best thing about this stain, however. After one good hit, even a seasoned smoker with a high tolerance will begin to feel the effects of this strong indica. This effective medicine may cause happiness, sleepiness, increased appetite, relaxation, and dry mouth. A fantastic choice for the evening or when being productive is not important.

We live in a different world today, and we are all well aware of the changed business environment and our transformed professional relations. The weirdest CF movies, all too popular in the 80s, couldn't predict the influence of the technology on our everyday communication and the simplest work tasks. Internet has become nowadays our official office and VoIP had taken over the meetings, seminars, conferences, conversation and every type of contact in a workplace. It has become common to have a conference call with collaborators on a different continent, and IT service made that possible with their low-cost and free of charge connection. But how far have the help tools and high-tech gadgets evolved and which one would suit best to your business organization? You should want something that is dependable and works perfectly, but you need as well a tool that is easy for all of your contacts to use. It is great to obtain a lot of advanced features, but it's not so peachy when collaborators you're trying to communicate with can't figure out how to join you or do not have appropriate software program. Here are just some of the popular services you can chose from for your future online brainstorming: MeetingBurner Popular because its very easy to use interface and free service. No downloads are necessary for meeting attendees. This is a web office where you can hold meetings, host seminars (webinars now) and share your screen presentation and videos with other collaborators. A good trait is its recording feature, easy to storage and preserve, so you can join the meeting whenever suits you and easily catch up. There are tools that help transfer the recording to other formats like YouTube for example. It has a chat and VoIP features, but the sharing of the presentations and videos is reserved for the organizers of the meeting. There is also a new MeetingBurner mobile application, so the conference participants on the move are not chained to their cubicle. Yugma is highly innovative web conferencing service, great for sharing your screen and collaborating with your long-distance coworkers. Its weird name means unified collaboration and it is great for sharing ideas. With Yugma users have a sensation of an in-house meeting because it offers multiple platforms for them (the users of Mac, Windows and Linux can share desktops, mouse and keyboards). Yugma features audio conferencing, public and private chat, annotation, quick polls, whiteboard tools, VoIP and session recording. It is available through Skype integration and customization. The quality advantage is its investment in the security. Protection from data corruption and hackers is provided with 128-bit encryption. WebEx is a popular choice in the large enterprises for their web conference service. It has a good sound and video quality, not to mention the tools for working with groups like whiteboarding, note-taking, annotations... With WebEx you would get a great mobile access with iPad, iPhone, Android, Blackberry, or you can attend meetings on any 3g, 4g or Wi-Fi enabled device (just launch the meeting URL from a browser and no app download is required). There is a free trial period, but the price is $19/month and higher if you want more meeting participants. Twiddle -a website that is extremely popular meeting place for groups. It immerses people in the brainstorming and the exchange of the ideas, images, graphics... It is very convenient for the collaboration with your long-distance friends and colleagues with whom you can browse the internet and hold conference calls. You do not need an account, no downloads or plug-ins. It's free for Educational Users, but after a trial run of one month, it costs $14/month for Professionals, $49/month for Teams and 189/month for Business account. Google+Hangouts is an alternative you can chose. It is not specified to the business arena, and it does not have the features to help exchange presentations, but it is the most familiar to everyone and very easy to access and navigate through for all users. You just need about 30 seconds to install the Google voice and video plug-ins. For free you can create a hangout and invite coworkers and friends to a video chat by Gmail. It is available on the road by Wi-Fi enabled mobile, or if you download Google+app for Android, iPhone, iPad. Of course there are many more options that you can check out and try on a couple of weeks for free: GoToMeeting, GoToWebinar, Adobe Connect, Fuze Meeting, iLinc, iMeet, Join.me, Mikogo, Global Meet, Intercall, Jabbster, Sync.In, Vyew, Huddle, ShowDocument, ZOHO Meeting ..... However, even the smartest choice of these VoIP services and applications brings in a high risk factor and vulnerability, an easier way-in for hackers and viruses. The security is possible to achieve with a dedicated Managed Service which will monitor and preserve from intruders your choice of the new platform for long-distance communication and online conferencing.

I could probably crawl on the ceiling if I stuck enough Platinum Kush on me. But what a waste. Let's vaporize some. And then some... And then some... And then some... OMG! This bud hits forever! So much resin! Its so Robbin goddamn Thick! Nice start.
This weed is boom dynamite. And I prefer heavy, deeply felt sensations while stoned... and baby, this weed is nice. It does the trick. My fingers are just floating over these keys. And holy creeper alert! Put out an APB on a glowing faced kid writing a pot review. So, many of the bud's I vap, hit fast and upfront, like Sour D or Pineapple Express, but this Platinum Kush has a lag time, and its real nice. And get this! I got 5 solid pulls off my whip using the vap. There's two more in it for sure... I just had to tap out. Most weed, even my beloved Sour D, only yields about 3 good pulls before the bud in the hopper goes dry. But Platinum Kush is SO sticky and SO filled with its piney resin, that it just keeps giving vapor pull after vapor pull. Wow! And its a heavy vapor too... Which could be a potential downside in exchange for its yield and potency, that its thick on the lungs, more so than a less resin dense plant.
The high is very nice, and as I said earlier, it creeps. After I vap, I just go about my business, and observe what transpires. 
In its infant phase, the high is mellow... nice... and I was like, "ok, cool."; but its a creeper, so in about 3 minutes(i think), that mellow nice, started to ramp up in the area of my frontal lobe, until my head became a toasty warm quick silver beach, one all covered with warm white sand. Yummy in the Sunny! 
This isn't even my first vap session today. I had one earlier, before I played soccer in my league's am game. This bud is great for focus and movement, for intensity and alertness... I felt like spider-man. I know, it seems contradictory to 'be high' and to be an athlete, but... some of my childhood, a lot of it in fact, leaves me very sad at times, and very distracted. So much so, that many of the things I like to do, I cant enjoy doing, because the feelings are so rapacious in their attempt to 'get my attention'.
So, I find that this Platinum Kush does an excellent job of giving the body a very beautiful sensation, one that compliments the tone's of anxiety fear and hardship. The result, my activities are more enjoyable and free flowing... And that just feels good I suppose. 
But it certainly does not 'make' ones feelings or experiences 'go away'... for no weed is that good, except maybe, the weeds of one's own heart and mind.
So all and all. I give Platinum Kush high marks across the board. I'm amazed at how versatile it is. Good for sport, focus and tuning into the zone while exploring the body. And also, its buzz is extremely enjoyable to the senses in a way that would make movie watching, chess playing, reading, napping, and any sensual endeavors, a little more intense in feeling . The floaty wavy sensation that Platinum Kush offers, powerfully too I might add, is a beehive of sensation Platinum Kush is not for amateurs.
Damn, time fly's by on this high... E=MC couch. Its been a solid two hours of being anywhere from super stoned to not as much super stoned. I think i'll do some body-work now, and enjoy the somatic side of this high once I stop writing and using my head. 
Thanks much!

Sat down on the couch, got comfortable and had one of the best highs I've had in years. Everything felt better, everything was beautiful, everything was alright. 

Highly recommended! Feel-good weed :)

These meds I expected to be my favorite. They looked incredible and had a great smell. Upon examining, by far this was my first choice. I was a little disappointed when smoking. Don't get me wrong the meds were good, pretty potent however, I did find one seed in the gram I bought, and the taste was not as strong as I was hoping.
Meh...
I love smoking this one the taste is superb and im in a place where there is no med shop so its very hard to find it here but when you do I just get it all

It enabled me to sit down and really just chill out with a couple of my friends also I use it to sleep which also works an absolute treat i really recommend using in the later hours of your day because it really will "chill you out"
Its a nice strain head high for sure. Tastes amazing Burns slowly.

Just became number 1 on my list (for now)!  In a word, awesome!  Taste is extraordinarily smooth on both in and exhale (one hit pipe).  Visually a great looking bud with brilliant purple leaves mixed with burnt orange accents, nice hairs and lots of crystals!  Fantastic head buzz with moderate body affects but close to eliminates by chronic back pain.  Can go either way depending on your mood but I can go happily into couch lock or easily switch up to doing something active and feel great either side of the spectrum.  Last a good two hours or more (time seems to fly right by though).  Seems to pick up intensity in increments until a level euphoric, happy, with great sense of well being.  I rate this a perfect 10 in all categories and now first on my shopping list!  If you have not tried this I would definitely recommend it!!!
Wonderful skunky flavor, with very relaxing feelings....

This shit hits you like a god damn brick wall. Smoking it out of a bong, it has a familiar taste but the intensity of the smoke itself may be a turn off to some people. Very powdery, but I think it was just grown well; I got some GDP from the same dispensary and it was kiefy and powdery too. ATF is a classic sativa strain, if you haven't heard of it you haven't been smoking enough, it's wonderful and everyone should try it at least once.

Felt like this was the strain I had been looking for for a long time. 
As soon as I lit the flower, I was immersed in a truly menthol, sweet tea flavor, followed by a hint of cocoa powder, and a definite mint to finish it off. Worth buying for the taste and smell alone. 
In fact, as soon as I opened the canister, I was overwhelmed by the thick aroma of a nice damp forest and a hint of mint leaf and cocoa powder. It's aroma-therapy in itself.
I can't even begin to describe the effects I felt off of this strain. First of all, there was so much joy out of nowhere. I felt like I needed to meet some one, and tell them how much they mattered. Seriously, though, I felt at peace with the entire human race. And secondly, no matter how stressed I had been earlier that afternoon, all was quashed by the sheer purity and clarity provided when under the influence of this wonderful, beautiful herb. 

I would give this a 9.5/10. And I highly recommend this strain to anyone suffering from bi-polar disorder, Major Depression, anxiety, stress, PTSD, and a whole lot more.
Great stuff

Best strain I've had in years. 
Tasty, smells heavenly, and the high is pure, yet insanely enjoyable.
It is now my favorite strain it gave me a really good high the taste was great and the high was good I didn't get headaches or any of that it just felt good.
I love this strain. I feel amazing.

Smell is cheesy and musty with a hint of alfalfa. Odor is pleasant enough. Buds are dark green with orange hairs and yellow trichromes. Frosty, looks sugar coated.

A few hits in and i'm already feeling it. Colorful sensations with this one. Everything is getting silvery and vibrant, reminds me a bit of the time i mixed orange jack and xxx og. Very faint tingles, can't tell if its more of a head high or a body high, then again i was never good at those things. Pretty sure it is a hybrid, though, definitely a bit of both sativa and indica in there. 

Halfway through the bowl i'm already well baked to golden brown perfection. Actually the room has become very yellow red and orange, the whole place seems warmer and more vibrant. It seems hazy, like a haze strain, but with a glowy, radiant feeling. I don't think i've gotten anything like this without mixing strains before. Its doing some very cool hallucinogenic stuff with my depth perception. Space seems larger, more grand and wide angle. 

10 minutes in the body high has come in full effect. I'm very tingly now, its massaging itself around my entire body, i've turned my space heater on and it feels relaxing and nice, like i've stepped into a hot tub. Thats always a nice effect. I still feel alert, but relaxed. I have my wits about me. Just had to lay back and go, "yeah, oh yeah. that feels good." This body high would be amazing for sex.

30 minutes in it feels like its in between the larry OG and super silver haze. nice ride, the high changes as it goes on. Its not as strong anymore but still very pleasant, relaxing. Good for stress relief.

Overall this strain lived up to its name, for the visual and physical sensations, rather than the fact that it is somehow mindblowing. It was definitely very good, a real keeper.

This one was a creeper for sher. Vaped it at 411 F super smooth, very dry so grab your water. Earth, but other than that probably piney. This kind of focused me a little bit, but not to much made me lose track of time and calmed me down. If you're trying to think of something creative I highly recommend this and Lamb's bread for writers.

Very good pot, certainly worth picking up. It has a very pleasant citrus smell. Be sure you have eye drops with you! It starts with a thoughtful head high, after about half an hour comes a very relaxing stone. This sativa has a property of enhancing senses, which makes it great for listening to music or watching movies. And it makes you hungry. Very hungry. Food tastes wonderful by the way. After the high there is no real burn-out feeling, just a little sleepiness.
Very strong strain. Really enjoyable.

Just wow, this strain is outstanding! The THC levels in the batch I got was 20.38%. Once I started smoking this (about a bowl pack .4G) the first thing I noticed was the taste. It related to the taste of fruit, just very very sweet. I really enjoyed it.

The high took about 7 minutes to get to it's peak point. At first right after I smoked I started to get a buzz. A very smooth buzz. I went inside and sat down and all the sudden I wanted to start doing things. I vacuumed, did the dishes and started my laundry. Ha, that only lasted for about 30 minutes. Then I was couch locked playing games for about a hour and a 15 minutes. Then my high started to fade, it you still are going to feel "funny" for a while even after your high is gone. But I didn't experience much of that because well...I smoked again! This strain looks amazing also, full with crystals, is light green, some orange hair and tint of purple. One of the best looking strains I had. But, the bud gets very shaky if touched a lot. It was sort of..dry. This bud also made my whole house smell. I purchased a QP of this bud, pictures will be attached if that is possible.

I got this strain from a good friend, who knows a lot about strains and he informed me this was called Chemo Kush. I have never heard of this strain before, so I was very curious to try it. He said it was really good and that it was easier to get ripped off of it. How could I say no to that, so I bought an 1/8th. I tried to find it on leafly, but I couldn't so I decided to write a review. 

First Impression: Look's like your typical bud, dark green with a little brown here and there. The thing that initially set this bud apart from the others was it's amazing smell. The smell is very different from other buds and it is very pleasing to the senses. 

Upon Further Inspection: The bud breaks up in an average manner. When you break up a nug, feast your eyes upon trichomes after trichomes. Very frosty and it looks very enjoyable.

Smoking It: I personally smoked out of a bowl and once a vaporizer with this bud. The Vaporizer high is good, and it is extremely calming. The bowl high is significantly better. When you are actually smoking, it will go straight to your head and may get a bit dizzy. One bowl pack and you can get stoned if you are a newbie or lightweight. Two bowl packs and you should be solid if you have been smoking for a bit or have a higher tolerance. Three bowl packs may get a veteran pretty high, but if you are a casual or intermediate smoker, you will be ripped. 

Smell: The smell of this bud once lit up is beautiful. It doesn't even smell like bud at all to be honest. It smells like a very strong cologne.

The High: The High is very relaxing. After you are done smoking and the dizziness stops, there is only good vibes to be found. The bud makes you happy, aroused, and giggly.

The Cons: Dizziness or very fast heartbeat when initially smoked. 

I give this a 4/5, it's high is worth a 3.5, but the smell is very good so I gave it a 4. Definitely worth trying if you can find it, or if it even exists, because this just maybe another strain of bud.

I started hallucinating, I was the center of the world and I was looking in on everything else through a tube. I was away from everyone and I felt fucking amazing. I was in a whole new world. Clone Only Strains - Smelliot
Often referred to as "the little sister" of Sour Kush, Smelliot is made from the same genetic cross, but is a bit milder and less psychedelic than the Sour.
Sativa-dominant hybrid
Scent: Pine, fuel, menthol, with a backing citrus Kush element - very pungent (hence the name).
Flavor: A bit of a sweeter Kush flavor with strong soil notes dominates, with elements of the sharper pine, fuel, and citrus elements from the smell creeping in at times.
Effects: Much like its sister the Sour Kush, Smelliot starts off with a strong package of Sativa effects immediately, filling the head and eyes with pressure and adding some delay to mental activities. The spaciness continues as the effect builds over the first 15 minutes, culminating in a rush of thoughts and internal energy that makes doing much of anything a bit difficult. Cerebral and almost racy gives way to a much more relaxing state in the latter half of the duration, with the body calming down and the mind feeling positive and clear. Recommended for Sativa-lovers who can handle the initial rush - its a good creativity and mood-boosting strain, making anxiety melt away in the 2nd half.

When it wore off, I was tired and but felt pretty good.  I ate a Wendy's chocolate frosty after.

Plain and simple, I think I just smoked too much for my tolerance level.  If you can handle potent stuff (This Blue Dream from my dispensary tested at 27%-ish THC), this strain will serve you well.  If you cannot, this strain should be fine, just take it very slow,1 hit at a time (wait 30 minutes), or you might find yourself caught off guard by its effects. I highly recommend.

After about an hour or two of continually smoking, the energizing effects gave way to overpowering fatigue. Within fifteen minutes of noticing my extreme tiredness, I was fast asleep. After smoking this strain exclusively for two weeks, I can assuredly say this happened every night. The only omnipresent effect throughout the different stages of the high was hunger. This strain makes you EAT. And eat. And then, just when you think your stomach will rupture from how much food you've crammed in there, you can't help but eat again.

Tasty and energetic sativa effects to start, but this strain might not be best for those who want hours upon hours of creative, uplifting, focused capacity. If you're looking for a relaxing night at home full of veg and limited couch lock, this may be the strain for you.

BUD:  Taste just like it smells, very skunky with a hint of lemon
LUNG EXPANSION:  Very low.  On a scale of 1-10 I'd say about a 2.
BODY/HEAD:  Hit's my head first, then slowly feel this moving down into my body. 
FLAVOR:  More of an earthy flavor.  Heavy skunk taste (or what I would imagine a skunk must taste like, since I've never tasted one... lol.)

It's been my pleasure to taste a beautifully hand crafted grow from Australia in both its first and second budding utilising the Sensei Star strain[1].  As you may recall the first grow elicited an amazing nose of "soft citrus lemon hints" - the taste was "eye-opening earthy sour", finishing with "berry and butter".  Naturally, I was a bit worried that the second grow would be a shadow of its first grow, and so I decided to allow the buds to age over a month. 

Upon opening the sealed glass jar I am hit with a rich berry and butter smell that has the same eye-opening and mouthwatering affects but somehow feels more distinguished and soft. This isn't a pungent-skunky smell, rather it is a vapour of aged vines and deep forest.  My first vapouriser hit [2] is like walking into a pine forest, your feet crunching acorns on the forest floor as the woodland fills your senses.  The taste is of green hops which excites the mind and speeds-up thinking.  The mid-range is a hint of grapefruit and the finish is the zing you get from gargling mouthwash in the morning.  On the whole, it leaves you feeling refreshed, relaxed and alert.  

My hat is off to the care and love that could produce two such wonderfully different grows with the same strain, we can only hope Australia will leagalise so Colorado growers can compete with Australian growers to produce even better products (as they do with wine).

[1]= http://www.leafly.com/indica/sensi-star
[2]= Utilising an Aerizer Solo: starting at setting no.2 (365F) for ten minutes, then to setting no.3 (383F) for five minutes and finishing on setting no.6 (401F) for ten minutes.  Water breaks between each sesh to cleanse pallet.

I love this strain! This is a pure sativa that is simply amazing. It's smell and flavor are a low-key earthiness. Nothing strong, nothing particularly memorable in either taste or smell. The best word for this weed is gentle. It's a gentle weed. (It's also potent as all get out, so don't mistake my use of the word gentle with lack of potency.) Here's what I mean: each hit from my pipe was smooth, mellow, and had no strong flavors so to speak, gentle; the lift was smooth, very smooth, so smooth that I didn't realize how baked I was, which was extremely. The high was as close to a head-only high as I've ever experienced, there is some body high going on, but it's subtle, my mind was where it was at. Many hours later I was gently placed back down. The smoothness of the whole experience is what makes this particular strain so exceptional. Gentle smoke, gentle lift off, intense but gentle high, and the gentlest let down ever. One word of warning, this is a true sativa. If you smoke this before bed, don't expect to get any sleep. I made that mistake, and my mind was racing all night, I didn't sleep at all, and oddly, I didn't care. This is a day weed.

I've started getting better at resisting the sleepiness this strain enduces. It still makes me just as sleepy, but I've been staying up up through the sleepiness for longer the more I use it. Instead of suffering from insomnia and falling asleep at 6am, I'm so mentally high that I pay far too much attention to the smallest details in whatever it is that I'm doing; which, in turn, has me staying up until 2am on something I should have been done with by midnight because I keep getting lost in small details. I suffer from chronic tension headaches.  I've tried about 10 strains and my favorite so far is Blue Dream.  When I first smoked it I thought I would get a little relaxed and stoney as usual, but man within 15 min I was starting to feel really happy and euphoric.  I really thought it had to be laced with something cuz it was so euphoric.  Sometimes I get a little panicky smoking weed, but this BD was like waves of happiness flowing in in subtle waves every 20 minutes or so.  No anxiety or panic at all...very gentle and a little spacey.  At one point I felt like shouting how good I felt.   I always go to the dispensary and get BD (Chemdawg/Headband too). Its cheap, and I am never disappointed.   Its kind of like going on a euphoria rollercoaster so beware it might make you a little manic.  Now,  I make it into firecrackers and eat a whole cracker and am on Planet 9 for about 5 hours or so.   I'm so euphoric I could care less about my headache :-).  I love watching stupid movies medicated with BD even though my attention goes in and out cuz I'm stoned.   And when the effects wear off I usually think "that was really fun!"  I hope this strain is always available and/or they come up with something better.   I also think it would do wonders for treatment resistant depression and mood disorders.

Currently writing this after two bong rips of Chemdawg. 

Feeling euphoric, happy, creative, no stress, no depression.

My pain is gone, completely. My hands do not lock when I close them. (Huge for me.)

The nugs, which I got from SpoCannabis in Spokane, are dense, tight, super-frosty, and so covered with orange hairs that each bud appears to have patches of orange interspersed with the frosty green. I'm freaking in love with the look of these nugs. They are gorgeous.

Not a strong smell, even when shredded; somewhat woody, piney, a little chemical/diesel.

Third bong rip for taste and feel: It's slightly harsh, not as nice a mouth/lung feel as some. As to the taste, mild, woody, very slightly pine, a hint of diesel, not strong at all.

Fourth bong rip 'cause I wanted to finish my bud while it was still freshly shredded... I'm completely baked.

Yet, I'm not even remotely couch locked. When I finish this review, I'm going to read a bit, listen to some music, cook something wonderful and watch a movie. 

After four bong rips the only negatives I feel are dry eyes, which are not that bad, and a very mild dry mouth which I'm going to take care of with a cup of tea.

There seems to be some confusion here between Critical Mass and Critical Kush.  Critical Mass is from the breeder CBD crew and has a 1:1 ratio of THC to CBD.  Average is 5% THC (and 5% CBD).  It's primarily for medical patients who need pain relief but don't want to get high.

People looking for a strong THC high (up to 20% or more) and a higher than average CBD (in this case 1.2%) want Critical KUSH.  That is an entirely different strain and is from the breeder Barney's Farm.

But claims of 18% THC in Critical Mass are just wrong.

https://www.cannabis-seeds-bank.co.uk/cbd-crew-seeds-critical-mass/prod_273.html

https://www.cannabis-seeds-bank.co.uk/barneys-farm-critical-kush/prod_70.html

So I will write a review on the new retail product. I have tried all 3 varieties, Relaxed, Awake, and Chai(felt like relaxed). I have to say that without a doubt Dixie makes the highest quality edible product on the market. I bought a 10count tin of each of the varieties and here's what I thought of each. Taste on all had a small but noticeable weed flavor, but it was easily masked by the mint flavor of Relaxed and Awake and went well with the Chai flavor as well. The mints were softer and broke apart quickly and easily. It took me 1 mint and about an hour and 10min. for full effect with effects starting about an hour post dosing. For me the 10mg was perfect, functionally I was all there, but pain at bay. At 20mg or (2)mints I noticed I was border line close to having a bad time. I was able to manage simple things, but felt strongly medicated. It lasted about 5 1/2 hrs. With the Awake effects were typical  Sativa with more energy and drive. The Chai felt a bit more balanced with the great body high minus the couch lock. The Relaxed felt almost like full couch lock with extreme hunger followed by an un-fightable urge to sleep at around 4hrs. post dosing. I can say it is the best sleep that I have ever gotten both natural or with any other strain/medication. Overall Chai was my favorite of the 3 in terms of effects and after a hard day I prefer Relaxed. All three of the flavors are amazing just like every other product I've tried.

Nomenclature and Politics aside, the flower is able to speak for itself.  Fully formed calyxes like lavender petals, two toned, rich sage green and deep purple often on the same calyx, inside and outside like a reversible jacket.  It has a pungent skunkish aroma like OG Kush, with sweeter notes of berry and fruit.  A Pleasure to smoke, I miss it when I don't have it.  The high is exceptional and pure feeling, no headaches with this beauty.

It's anthocyanin purple is found in produce that are regarded as "Super Foods", blueberries, blackberries, acai and the like.  Green leaves are able to turn blue and red light into energy with ease but it cannot absorb light of its colour, purple leaves thrive on this excess energy - even gaining nourishment from some of the light that is reflected off of its green neigbours! All in all, this is the most medicinal strain I've encountered, and it is my every day go to strain.

About an hour later, I still felt high but felt much better. I initially thought that this was a sativa strain as I'd never felt like this before and I'd heard horror stories of getting high when hungry; which is something I like to with indicas so I can demolish some munchies but even eating before hand hasn't helped. This is not a bash at weed guys, I've been smoking a long time but this strain made me want to quit. Smoked some later with a lot less weed and the effects were the same just not as amplified and nowhere near as bad. I bought a 20 bag literally 2 weeks before christmas and I still have 2 joints worth left and I don't know if I'll smoke it.

World of Seeds Bank - Skunk 47
Skunk 47 is the result of crossing Skunk#1 mother, which was the first real indica-sativa hybrid comprising Afghan, Mexican and Colombian genetics and which changed the face of cannabis culture across the globe, with the famous AK 47, mainly sativa hybrid that has an ultra quick flowering cycle and a very fruity taste. Although, the genetics of both are similar in many respects, by crossing them it's improved many of these shared characteristics, resulting in a bushy, vigorously growing indica that produces great yields; highly valued commercially for her compact buds and very intense Skunky taste and aroma.

Genotype: 10% sativa / 90% indica

Yield: 400-500g indoor

Aroma: Skunky, Wet Leather Shoes
Effect: Well balanced, could get narcotic at high doses
THC: 20%
Resistance to Mould: High
Resistance to Pests: High
Medicinal Value: High

First of all the smell is EXTREMELY pungent and can be smelled through many plastic bags and even medicine canisters. It looks almost engineered in how it grows into healthy fat and dense buds that are COVERED in Orange-Red hairs and white THC crystals. It is the most distinct smelling and looking strain I've ever come by. I was hesitant at first because the smell and amount of white crystals and kief in between the dense almost unnatural looking amount of hairs, some of which were thicker placed almost looking like tree moss. To be honest at first I thought it was laced or compacted herb but no I can assure the buyer it sure is Sativa. It is a mix between strong lemon/grapefruit/citrus and ammonium scent. It is a little pungent for my liking but friends love it. I have noticed it is hard to judge how much to smoke as it doesn't have the sleepy cutoff of Indica. I have noticed it is very ineffective in treating my depression and PTSD, as my mind usually functions at a high rate normally (diagnosed with multiple depression and add issues). On this strain I go ADD on everything or am stuck on one topic for hours. By that I mean my browser will have 15+ tabs ranging from different videos, articles, descriptions, pictures, social media, etc. when I am in a good mood and smoke, also good for video gaming. BUT, when I am depressed as I am now and have some nonviolent PTSD, it is basically a one way focus on my biggest suffering in which I cannot smoke more and escape from. So basically it enhanced my PTSD and depression and multiplied the feelings while making my mind so focused on that one thing that I cannot escape or relieve myself of suffering until I fall asleep by taking an ambien. It is a real hit or miss strain for me. Best recommended for college students wanting to focus on homework or on research assignments and or cramming before finals. Can be a social clear-headed day strain.

NOT FOR DEPRESSION, ANXIETY, PARANOIA, OR ANY MENTAL ILLNESS RELATED TO DEPRESSION OR ANXIETY! 

This is a strain for the *happy* average college student or any kind of worker really. It can be energizing, enhancing in focus and brain power, and uplifting in the search for knowledge. It is a relatively clear headed high that doesn't have a low over-do limit like most Indicas and Hybrids. 

Others have recommended it for Depression, PTSD, and Anxiety but I highly advise AGAINST doing that. I suffer from all three and usually have a lightly enhanced level of paranoia no matter what strain I smoke. That being said this strain made my mind so focused on the feelings that are bringing me the most suffering, while energizing me so I can't easily fall asleep to escape. No matter what I've done to get myself out of fits after smoking this while feeling lost, I could not. My mind would go directly back to that negative feeling and images flashed in my mind of memories tied to the cause of the suffering. As you could imagine, not too fun. 

About it: It looks fake, to put it bluntly. It is the most distinct strain in many ways that I've come across. It is PUNGENTLY lemon/ammonia smelling that is overpowering sometimes to some, very pleasurable for others. It also gives the appearance of being fake because it buds in dense fat nuggets that are lighter green and almost covered in THC and vibrant colored hairs. HAIRS everywhere! Definitely one of the hairiest strains I have ever seen, and I have had it tested to make sure it wasn't some other herb compress or fake weed. It is indeed just a very distinct and bold strain of Sativa. 

I would recommend buying a small amount and seeing how it effects you. I've seen positive and negative reviews for Depression, Anxiety, ADD/ADHD, and mental disorders so it seems the strain chooses the smoker in a way. 

Give it a shot if you have taken or have needed to take medications like Ritalin, Adderall, Welbutrin, or similar drugs. Or if you are one of those college "dopers" cramming for finals.

The pre-1998 strain of Bubba Kush has always been on my personal top 5 list of favorite hybrids.  Many of us that grew up in Southern California and during the 'Generation-Y' era feel a deep, personal connection to this strain as we smoked it in many of our early experiences with marijuana.  These genetics first became widely available at some of the 1st medical dispensaries in LA during the 90's.

Pre-98 Bubba Kush is well known as a cannabis containing several STRONG flavors.  As I smoke this, filtered out of a heavy, beaker bottom JBD, the most prominent tastes and smells I associate with this bud are skunk and citrus smells followed by the strong distinct orange citrus flavor from the classic OG Kush that mothered this hybrid.  Another obvious flavor your taste buds pick up quickly is a strong 'earthiness' that I like to explain as tasting exactly like wet soil, perfect for gardening.  There are a couple fairly subtle notes that I always detect in Bubba which include coffee and pine.

The beauty of the pre-98 Bubba Kush may ellipse both it's smell and taste.  The plant has some of the most perfectly trimmed, shaped and crystallized buds known to man and has been known to yield large quantities. 

My favorite thing about pre-98 Bubba Kush is the amazing high it gives you!!  Both body and heady, this high has been known to put me in any type of mood I want to be in at that time making it #3 on my favorite buds of all time list!  If I have a lot of work to do that day, this bud has gotten me though these projects in record time.  If I want to go fishing all day, this bud will give me the most fun fishing experience possible!!!  It's a very versatile cannabis.

Keep on chiefin'
-The Weedman

The Island Sweet Skunk I am smoking right now is from a new local pot shop in Colorado.  It produces a very heady, uplifting and hazy high.

Although it's not widely known as a bud with pronounced flavors, the Island Sweet Skunk strain can actually be very flavorful!  If you have a well grown batch, you can taste a very pronounced sweetness to the bud that contains faint notes of vanilla, nutmeg, and sometimes butter.  As you exhale, these notes fade into notes of honey and almost a molasses taste.  Along with the vanilla, I sometimes taste the indistinct flavor of Fall which I think is actually a hint of red apple.

This Colorado grown Island Sweet Skunk almost gives you the feeling that you are floating a few inches above the ground, or the chair you're sitting in, while at the same time, you are surrounded by a very light fog.  This fog is almost completely invisible, except for the opaque feeling of a smoke-like substance layered between you and the existential items within your view.  Physically, there is a strong tingling sensation behind my eyes in addition to other areas of my face like my cheeks.

Keep smoking,
-The Weedman

White Widow is a memorable strain for me, and not just because it was the first one I smoked. Even after years of daily smoking and vaporising, this strain's indica side still floors me.

It's scent and flavour are quite plain and natural, a simple earthen taste with a touch of wood.

The first few seconds of a hit will have you calm and relaxed (if not coughing madly), followed by a heavy couchlock that will leave you reaching for your favourite drink and snacks if not your bed.

I have trouble recommending this strain for medical use, as its effects aren't gentle at all. It hits ridiculously hard, and its sativa side will leave your mind wandering more than desired. Smoke with caution, and avoid combining White Widow with busy situations.

No head rush, no body high, just a gentle buzz worth maybe $1.50. So one of two things happened here: Either I got ripped off by my provider (unlikely for several reasons) or there is no such thing as "Jack Herer" or any other strain label - cultivators, dispensaries & dealers just use whatever the fuck name they think will move product at the moment. I've seen that argument made convincingly elsewhere by industry researchers. Cause there may be some knock-out Jack Herer somewhere, but that sure as shit ain't what I got. And this is yet another reason we need legalization: to "weed" out the crooked assholes who pawn weak shit as top shelf.

Ah, Blue Cheese.   This strain had quite a profound effect on me:  It left me relaxed and sedated like an Indica, but provided a smooth, focused, and hazy-free mental clarity that evoked an artistic and creative mood out of me. 

I've tried this train both in small rooms, concerts, large crowds, and in the forest and I have to say this:

If you are incredibly sensitive to anything evoking the slightest bit of an anxiety, you may not wish to smoke this in a small room as I have experienced a bit of restlessness and anxiety from being in a small room.  This strain tends to get your thoughts flowing, so if you're not prepared for that I urge caution. 

However, all around this strain is quite pleasurable.  I can smoke a bowl or two, or one toke, or whatever...and still enjoy a nice body stone whilst being able to withold a conversation with another human being without using the words, "Dude bro, like...wo man, dude...wait, what?"

I would recommend this for daytime use around the house, if you are suffering any pain and need to have relief during the day without falling alseep standing up, or if you are wanting to enjoy a relaxing evening with someone without having to smoke a sativa to stay awake.  This hybrid has the best of both worlds.

My first expirence with CFL growing with an auto-flower strain grew out of the lack of space of a grow tent. It was grown Hydroponic deep water culture using the Lucas Formula with General Hydroponic nutrients. Used a T-5 4bulb 24" fixture with CFL's for suppliment lighting. Light cycle was 24/7. Ph maintained at 5.8. At about 3 weeks into Veg the plant was topped and a scrog net was installed about 8" above the plant so the side branching from the sides of the could be spread to promote lateral growth. The total amout of time saved as opposed to growing a non-auto strain was about 2 weeks. Growth was very impressive from a t-5 as I've always used 600w HPS for flowing.. Yeild was about 2.5 OZs. using scrog. Could have cured and flushed a little better but had to hurry and harvest because we were moving into a new place. The high was very clear and slowed time a bit, but the effect was almost instant. The flavor was kind of piney with a bit of musky after taste. High lasted about 45 mins to 1 hour after a hefty bowl. Pretty easy to grow, this grow was done in a closet. Temps were 75-80 F. Humidity was right at 50% with no Humidifier or suppliment moisture. Not really a strain to worry about as far as smell is concerned. Highly reccomended for first time growers or peeps with little space to work with. Good stoney smoke but not going to knock your socks off or turn you into a zombie. Play video games, or watch a movie or somthing. Didn't make me wanna workout or go for a bike ride. I'm not one to get super euphoric on weed (more chilled out and with Sativas creative, thoughtful etc.) but Purple Urkle did a good job at making me feel very content with life. Many of my stressors, while still technically "there", did not concern me. I was able to just focus on the moment.  Definitely great. The "Real McCoy" (RMC) is a Hybrid (NOT Sativa) strain and part of a 'Private Reserve' batch that I discovered at Daily Dabs Wax Bar in East LA.  This is a 'must try' for those in search of a strain that will keep you high, not stoned.  I believe this to be more on the Sativa influence, due to it's high.

The budtender had recommended it and said it helped him focus without any spaciness.  I am using it to treat my ADHD that I had been previously treating through Adderall and Vyvanse for almost 10 years.  I (and everyone else around me) got tired of the irritability and 'edge' it gave me, making me look and act like an a*shole!  I am glad I re-discovered the benefits of this magical plant.

Back to the RMCthe buds are nice, tight, and compact little 'nuggets', averaging in size, comparable to those large red globe grapes. RMC shows a fair amount of red hairs and lots of juicy crystals.  A citrus-like smell while fresh, as well as while smoking or vaping, it is a turns out to be your nice daytime "cup o' coffee", but without the jitters.  Light-medium smoke with a zesty finish of citrus. 

Onset is fairly quick to come on (5-10 min) and keeps you high for about an hour or so, depending on your tolerance level.  It is a nice, cerebral, behind-the-eyeballs kind of high, with no 'stoned' or 'couch-lock' feelings.  Fully functional daytime, 'active' high that allows for concentration and awareness.

Daily Dabs Wax Bar is just north of County USC Med. Center.  They are at the the beginning of Main St., where Mission Rd. and Valley Blvd. merge together.  Look for the neon green cross.

323.671.8129 | 321 N. Main St, LA 90031 | 10am-11pm, 7 days)

I am neurotic, suffer from chronic lower back pain, anxiety, stress, and IBS. I smoked a strain labeled "Blueberry" in 2009 (I was in Berkeley). I usually suffer from intense paranoia (locked up, not talking, panicking, trapped in my own thoughts) but I experienced the opposite on Blueberry. I was alert, happy, and extremely talkative. I had a rad night the first time I smoked it. I tried a different strain (a kush... not sure what) the next night and was couch-locked, itchy and paranoid. The night after that, Blueberry again and I was elated. I conserved the rest of the bag by only taking small doses throughout the day as needed for relief. I don't know if the Blueberry strain of 2014 is going to be the same everywhere, but if it is, I recommend giving it a try if you usually get paranoid. However, different strains effect some of us differently, like any other medication, so if you have a panic attack don't blame me.

After the release of the popular stoner flick by the same name, many people assumed that Pineapple Express was a fictional strain, but the truth is it is a very real bud, a cross between Trainwreck and Hawaiian, both heavily influenced by sativa genes.  It is this background that makes Pineapple Express such a popular strain.  The jubilant sativa high can completely change your day and is very different from the mostly indica based strains popular on market.  You will want this medication in your life, and you will become giddy when you see it on a menu.  

Pineapple Express is a shiny bud, bright with trichromes, making for a pale green bud.  Juxtaposed against this pastel flower are orange hairs grouped in thick clumps.  When I broke it up, a fine layer of kief was left on the bottom of my dish, speaking to the number of crystals covering these buds.  The smell of this strain is sweet and succulent and lingered on my fingers long after I handled it.  There is a mouth watering effect when the tropical aroma is deeply inhaled.  While pineapple is assumed, it is more mango and pear: both luscious and juicy.  Tearing into this bud is like ripping into an off-the-branch-fresh fruit.  The flavor, although sweet in the green hit, is astringent in the exhale and can be harsh.  This can be the case with some sativas types.  

Although Pineapple Express has some Afghani indica in its Trainwreck heritage, this is a predominantly sativa high.  Its been touted as the happiest of highs--completely relaxed and carefree.  Medicating with Pineapple Express is a bit like going on vacation.  Even though it is mellow and cheerful, there is little chance you are going to get much work done.  This strain is distracting, and I had a hard time achieving much of anything.  It is much better enjoyed when responsibility can be shelved and the high can truly be enjoyed.  Id strongly recommend this strain as an effective antidepressant.  It helps you forget yourself and unwind.  In todays hectic world, it can be your stolen moment to center yourself.

After reviewing four straight indicas, I've lately felt run down and tired.  I have always preferred uplifting sativas, the type that set you going and give you the feeling like you can take on the world.  OCPC has grabbed a winner with their Strawberry Diesel.  Although there is some Afghani indica tucked into the NYC Diesel, overall, this was the euphoric sativa for which I was looking.  

The buds of this strain are a flush green.  Blended in among the flowers are hairs so faintly red that they are almost pink, a nice touch for a strain with strawberry in its name.  If you think you see a seed pod in the picture above, you are correct.  It has just been the one seed so far, and it has gone in my drawer for a future grow.  One seed aside, this is a nice looking strain. It is slightly sticky from the dusting of trichromes.  There is a clear odor of strawberries, fresh and organic, not sweet like artificial candy flavors.  Unmistakably, fuel and grapefruit are also present in this strains profile.  The taste favors the diesel flavor of NYC Diesel.  Much of the fruitiness you notice in the smell gives way too harsh fuel when burnt.  However, even with this gruffness, there is little smokers fatigue.  

What I missed most during my run of indicas was the cerebral relief that sativas bring.  Along with arthritis pain and migraines, I often use my medical marijuana for work stress, anxiety, and at times, depression.  Strawberry Diesel is perfect for all three.  The high is happy and energetic.  The truest sign for me of whether a strains effects fall sativa or indica is what I do immediately after smoking.  If I sit there, mindlessly watching tv or messing around online like I have been all week, its most likely an indica.  If I get up, grab my keys, and get out the door or take out my computer to start working, like I have been with Strawberry Diesel, then we are dealing with a top notch sativa.  Id recommend this strain as a daytime treatment for any number of psychosomatic symptoms.  It will leave you hopeful and excited, roused to take on the day.

John Muir, while discussing the redwood forests of Northern California, remarked, Going to the woods is going home.  The comforting, warming high of Redwood Kush is reminiscent of sitting by a campfire, surrounded by friends and the company of looming sugar pines.  Cozy and satisfying, there is something familiar about this strain, like its taking you home.  

While I wouldnt classify these nuggets as popcorn, they are small, bite sized buds.  Redwood Kush would be a deep forest green color if it werent absolutely drowning in pale amber trichromes.  The buds look like a pair of dirty khakis after being worked into Sequoia National Forest for a hike.  The aroma continues this theme.  Much of the scent is pepper tree and cedar.  However, the scent is so sweet in its woodiness, that there is even some over-ripe berry and musky earth, turning it sour in the end.  I was pleased by how this indica smoked.  It wasnt harsh at all, and it had fine moments when it was like balsam or sandalwood incense.  Everything about the aesthetic side of this weed reminded me of northern California.  

The high of Redwood Kush is noticeably indica, meaning it exists mostly in the body.  I prefer the cerebral effects of sativas and sativa hybrids, and dont often donate for pure indicas.  However, Redwood is a breezy body high that is perfect for minor aches and pains.  It helped ease my arthritis and shoulder pain considerably, but did little for a migraine I came down with one night.  I also enjoyed this strain because there is no couch lock, no laziness, and no drowsy yawning.  This was the most dynamic indica Ive smoked, since coming to Southern California, and it is perfect as a sunny daytime medication.

I felt like trying something different when I headed to the dispensary. I usually prefer heavy indica or indica dominant hybrids. 

I asked for a recommendation.  He pulled out a few jars and Maui happened to be one of them. Very pungent smell. Beautiful dense buds, covered in crystals, almost blocking the view of the forest of yellow hairs. 

I headed home after a full day of not smoking, and packed my bong. 

The first hit was great. Smooth. Great flavors. Very sweet, but floral. Kinda what you'd expect a strain called Maui to taste like. 

I felt the cerebral high pretty quickly, but kind of mild. After finishing the bowl and watching some TV, it slowly started creeping up on me. 

After bowl #3 I was solid. Very mellow. Super relaxed. Slight tingling throughout my body, like warm water rushing over me. 

Now, at this point, you're thinking "Okay, sounds great! But wait, Stutterfiend, why only 3 stars?"

Well. I'm getting to that.

Although I felt very relaxed, I didn't feel couchlock. But I also didn't feel like getting up. Or changing the channel. Or doing anything really. I was just lazy. Kind of in the middle. 

Overall; I enjoyed Maui. Strong out the gate, but really slows down quickly.

This three-way hybrid, from the cross between the most powerful and productive varieties with rapid, vigorous growth and many branches, bursts into buds in the flowering stage.
Given its dimensions we dont recommend growing indoors in big pots.
Its large size makes it advisable for reduced spaces, small containers or late transplants, helping to control its height.
This plant reaches its peak outdoors. Sown in soil or large container, it grows vigorously to become a real monster, making the grower wonder if its really autoflowering.
The aromas and flavours of this variety have a fresh and spicy touch. Without forgetting its explosive power creating a cerebral high effect that raises its strength to the point of uncontrollable laughter.

Quasar, which comes from a pure indica and a backcrossed sativa, unifies the best of both strains into a choice hybrid. Highly vigorous growth that reduces indoor cultivation timing; it also yields radiant outdoor plants. It has a powerful structure that easily stands the weight of several buds, hard and compact to the point they seem pressed.

Astonishing potency, strong effect with a hard disposition to euphoria without nervousness.

With Quasar a perfect balance between indica & sativa has been achieved, it will surely satisfy sybarites for its quality as well as comercial growers for its quantity.

Pulsar is a non-autoflowering cross between Dutch and Central American sativas. One of the most peculiar attributes is its high production and big sativas charge. It has extremely vigorous growth and is tremendously expansive, so it is important to prune the tips of the plant if growing indoors, or to use the Screen of Green technique. If growing outdoors we recommend that you plant it towards the end of the season to avoid it growing to a monstrous size! Pulsars genetics give it a musky smell and a spice-like flavour, while its Haze background makes for an energising, stimulating effect which will eventually leave you laughing uncontrollably. It is not a plant as suitable for the novice growers and neither for inexperienced smokers. 
Flowering: 75 days.

After battling a few years of a torn bulging disc, panic attacks, recluse like behavior, and deep depression along with a corresponding pharmaceutical for each ailment and their side effects, I was borderline suicidal and felt like a burden. As a disabled vet, the VA never brings up marijuana as a legitimate medicine for serious issues. I was on morphine, clonopin, gabapentin, and a slew of SSRIs for almost 3 years like a zombie, sick and not getting better. This particular breed is very effective. I did a cold turkey of ALL meds then after that storm I tried some marijuana from a fellow vet who recommended it. Its was outdoor and really made me overly paranoid. So I tried a few others, and if you are suffering anxiety and panic from PTSD this is not a cure, but it works great compared to the side effects of "conventional" medicine. My zero to 100 on panic and anger have been governed to a point where I can spend all day with my 5 and 2 year olds solo and not lose my shit, which was a huge thing for me. I like that its Afghani descendant, since Afghanistan is where I got so fucked up. My pain level is decreased, no where near morphine levels, but Ill trade mild relief with no side effects over the demon of opiates any day. Anyways, long review, but Im a complete convert to medicinal marijuanas effectiveness and anyone who denies its medicinal value is a fucking moron. Thanks.
